{"step_index":18,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-07-18T06:42:15Z","thinking":"**Defining the Project's Scope**\n\nI've established the basic structure and am excited! The setup is indeed straightforward. My current focus is designing a clean Markdown guide, detailing how to run the code using Docker. The guide will be stored in `/home/hieu/.gemini/antigravity-cli/brain/71e25571-7166` and ensure it's user-friendly.\n\n\n","tool_calls":[{"name":"write_to_file","args":{"ArtifactMetadata":"{\"RequestFeedback\":false,\"Summary\":\"A detailed guide on how to run the v-nexus project using Docker Compose, including configuration, launch options (GPU vs CPU), verification, and troubleshooting.\",\"UserFacing\":true}","CodeContent":"\"# V-Nexus Docker Running Guide\\n\\nThis guide describes how to build, run, and manage the **V-Nexus Tutor** system using Docker Compose.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 📋 Prerequisites\\n\\nEnsure you have the following installed on your system:\\n- **Docker**: Engine version `20.10+` or newer.\\n- **Docker Compose**: V2 (run as `docker compose`) or standalone V1 (`docker-compose`).\\n- *(Optional)* **NVIDIA Container Toolkit**: If you wish to run the local LLM (**Ollama**) using GPU acceleration.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🛠️ Step 1: Configuration (`.env`)\\n\\nBefore starting the containers, verify or update the project's environment variables in the [.env](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/.env) file.\\n\\n### LLM Run Modes\\nYou can configure the project to use a cloud LLM or a local one:\\n1. **Cloud LLM (FPT AI)**: Set `LLM_MODE=fpt`. The system will connect to FPT Cloud's API using the `API_KEY` defined in the env file.\\n2. **Local LLM (Ollama)**: Set `LLM_MODE=ollama`. You will need to download/run the selected model (e.g., `qwen3:1.7b`) inside Ollama once it's up.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🚀 Step 2: Running the System\\n\\nDepending on your hardware capability (GPU vs CPU-only), choose one of the following methods:\\n\\n### Option A: Standard Mode (Recommended if you have a GPU)\\nThis runs the full suite defined in [docker-compose.yml](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/docker-compose.yml), assigning GPU resources to the `ollama` service.\\n\\nRun the following command in the project directory:\\n```bash\\ndocker compose up -d --build\\n```\\n*(If your system uses the older standalone Docker Compose v1, use `docker-compose up -d --build` instead.)*\\n\\n### Option B: Lite Mode (CPU-only / Low Specs)\\nThis runs the system using [docker-compose.lite.yml](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/docker-compose.lite.yml), which does not request GPU access and limits Ollama's memory usage to 2GB to prevent host resource starvation.\\n\\nRun:\\n```bash\\ndocker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml up -d --build\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\n<truncated 2643 bytes>","Description":"\"Create docker running guide for the v-nexus project\"","Overwrite":"true","TargetFile":"\"/home/hieu/.gemini/antigravity-cli/brain/71e25571-7166-4225-8338-32b4e3317b15/run_with_docker_guide.md\"","toolAction":"\"Creating Docker guide artifact\"","toolSummary":"\"Create Docker guide artifact\""}}],"truncated_fields":["tool_calls"]}
