{"step_index":20,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-07-18T06:42:20Z","content":"To run the **V-Nexus** project using Docker, you have two options depending on your system resource constraints and whether you want GPU support for the local LLM:\n\n### 1. Configure the Environment\nCheck the config in the [.env](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/.env) file. \n- By default, it's set to cloud mode (`LLM_MODE=fpt`) using FPT AI Inference with an API Key already filled.\n- If you change `LLM_MODE=ollama`, the system will use a local model via the Docker Ollama container.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Choose Your Run Option\n\nNavigate to your project directory `/home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC 2026/v-nexus` and run one of the following:\n\n#### Option A: Standard Mode (Recommended if you have a GPU)\nRuns the full stack using [docker-compose.yml](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/docker-compose.yml) (enables GPU reservations for Ollama):\n```bash\ndocker compose up -d --build\n```\n\n#### Option B: Lite Mode (CPU-only / Low Resources)\nRuns a lighter stack using [docker-compose.lite.yml](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/docker-compose.lite.yml) (runs Ollama on CPU and limits memory to 2GB):\n```bash\ndocker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml up -d --build\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Verify & Access Services\n\nOnce the containers are started, the services will be available at:\n* **Frontend (Dashboard):** [http://localhost:8081](http://localhost:8081)\n* **Gateway API (Swagger docs):** [http://localhost:8000/docs](http://localhost:8000/docs)\n* **MCP Server:** [http://localhost:8500/mcp](http://localhost:8500/mcp)\n\n**Default Logins:**\n* **Teacher:** `teacher1@vnexus.vn` / Password: `123456`\n* **Student:** `hs01@vnexus.vn` / Password: `123456`\n\n---\n\n### 📖 Details & Troubleshooting\nFor a comprehensive set of commands (checking status, pulling models manually, viewing individual logs, rebuilding without cache, and stopping), please refer to the detailed artifact guide I created:\n* [run_with_docker_guide.md](file:///home/hieu/.gemini/antigravity-cli/brain/71e25571-7166-4225-8338-32b4e3317b15/run_with_docker_guide.md)\n\n***\n\n**Summary of work completed:**\n- Researched directory structure and located compose configurations ([docker-compose.yml](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/docker-compose.yml), [docker-compose.lite.yml](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/docker-compose.lite.yml)).\n- Created a comprehensive Docker guide artifact ([run_with_docker_guide.md](file:///home/hieu/.gemini/antigravity-cli/brain/71e25571-7166-4225-8338-32b4e3317b15/run_with_docker_guide.md)) with configuration info, run commands, verification details, and troubleshooting instructions.","thinking":"**Assessing Docker Setup**\n\nI'm evaluating the user's Docker environment, or the lack thereof. The key seems to be enabling the user to run code with Docker, but I'm careful not to automatically execute Docker commands, especially `docker-compose`. I need to be more cautious about the best way to leverage Docker for them.\n\n\n"}
