{"step_index":51,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-07-18T06:44:05Z","content":"To test both **offline execution** and **prompt optimization** using Docker, you can configure the environment to use static fallbacks or run a local model inside Docker, and map volumes to instantly reload modified prompts.\n\nHere is the quick setup guide:\n\n### 1. Offline Testing Configurations\n\nYou can test two levels of offline capability by editing [.env](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/.env):\n\n* **Static Template Fallback (No LLM API calls)**:\n  Set `LLM_MODE=offline`. In this mode, the system bypasses all LLM calls and uses pre-written local templates in [tools/plan_tool.py](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/tools/plan_tool.py).\n* **Fully Offline Local LLM (Ollama)**:\n  Set `LLM_MODE=ollama` and `OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen3:1.7b` (or `8b`). Start the services using Docker:\n  ```bash\n  docker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml up -d --build\n  ```\n  Then pull the local model inside the Ollama container:\n  ```bash\n  docker compose exec ollama ollama pull qwen3:1.7b\n  ```\n  Once the model is loaded, you can disconnect your computer from the internet completely and test prompt/agent behaviors.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Prompt Optimization and Live Code Reloading\n\nSystem prompts are defined in [tools/plan_tool.py](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/tools/plan_tool.py) (e.g. `_STUDENT_SYSTEM_PROMPT`) and [domain/sme_innovation_adapter.py](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/domain/sme_innovation_adapter.py).\n\nTo prevent having to rebuild your Docker images after editing system prompts, add **volume mounts** to the `gateway` service in [docker-compose.yml](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/docker-compose.yml):\n\n```yaml\n  gateway:\n    ...\n    volumes:\n      - ./agent:/app/agent\n      - ./tools:/app/tools\n      - ./domain:/app/domain\n      - ./gateway/app:/app/app\n```\n\nNow, any changes you make locally to system prompts or response validation logic will take effect immediately inside Docker.\n\n---\n\n### 🔍 Complete Walkthrough & Best Practices\nI have generated a comprehensive guide detailing step-by-step instructions on local LLM setup, configuring hot-reloads, safety post-validation checking, and querying endpoints to test output structures:\n* [testing_guide.md](file:///home/hieu/.gemini/antigravity-cli/brain/71e25571-7166-4225-8338-32b4e3317b15/testing_guide.md)\n\n***\n\n**Summary of work completed:**\n- Reviewed how prompts are generated and dispatched in [tools/plan_tool.py](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/tools/plan_tool.py) and [agent/llm_client.py](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/agent/llm_client.py).\n- Produced [testing_guide.md](file:///home/hieu/.gemini/antigravity-cli/brain/71e25571-7166-4225-8338-32b4e3317b15/testing_guide.md) to outline static fallback tests, Ollama offline setup, volume mounts for prompt testing, and the prompt verification process."}
