{"step_index":63,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-07-18T07:02:52Z","content":"Based on the `docker compose ps` output, your core containers (**db**, **gateway**, **mcp_server**, and **frontend**) are successfully up and running. \n\nHowever, **Ollama** is not running. Attempting to start the standard Ollama container returns an NVIDIA driver error:\n> `nvidia-container-cli: initialization error: nvml error: driver not loaded: unknown`\n\nThis happens because the standard [docker-compose.yml](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/docker-compose.yml) requests NVIDIA GPU access, but your host system does not have NVIDIA GPU drivers loaded.\n\nDepending on what you want to do, here are your options:\n\n---\n\n### Option A: Test using Cloud LLM (FPT AI) right now\nThe current setup is running in **FPT Cloud LLM Mode** (`LLM_MODE=fpt`), which does not require Ollama.\n1. Open your browser and navigate to:\n   * **React Dashboard (Frontend):** [http://localhost:8081](http://localhost:8081)\n   * **API Docs (Swagger UI):** [http://localhost:8000/docs](http://localhost:8000/docs)\n2. Log in using the default credentials:\n   * **Username**: `teacher1@vnexus.vn`\n   * **Password**: `123456`\n3. You can test prompt responses in real time via the UI.\n\n---\n\n### Option B: Test local Offline/LLM capability (using CPU)\nTo run Ollama on your CPU without requiring NVIDIA GPU drivers, you need to switch to the Lite compose file:\n\n1. **Stop the running services:**\n   ```bash\n   docker compose down\n   ```\n\n2. **Start the Lite stack (CPU-only configuration):**\n   ```bash\n   docker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml up -d --build\n   ```\n\n3. **Verify all services (including Ollama) are running:**\n   ```bash\n   docker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml ps\n   ```\n\n4. **Pull the Qwen model inside Ollama:**\n   ```bash\n   docker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml exec ollama ollama pull qwen3:1.7b\n   ```\n\n5. **Update your configuration to use local LLM:**\n   * Open your [.env](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/.env) file.\n   * Change `LLM_MODE=ollama`.\n   * Recreate the gateway service to load the new `.env` settings:\n     ```bash\n     docker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml up -d --force-recreate gateway\n     ```\n\n6. **Test offline:** You can now disconnect from the internet and query the application.\n\n***\n\n**Summary of work completed:**\n- Inspected active Docker Compose configurations and diagnostic logs.\n- Identified that standard Ollama failed to start due to missing host GPU drivers.\n- Provided actionable instructions for both testing immediately via Cloud API, and switching to the CPU-based offline testing configuration.","thinking":"**Analyzing the Log Error**\n\nI've hit a snag. The `docker compose up -d ollama` command failed. The error message is clear: \"driver not loaded.\" It's an NVIDIA driver issue because the compose file is trying to use a GPU, which this host doesn't have. Looks like I'll need to adjust the configuration to proceed.\n\n\n"}
