{"step_index":65,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-07-18T07:21:02Z","content":"The command to start Ollama failed because pulling the `ollama/ollama:latest` image (which is about 3.27 GB) timed out on your network:\n> `failed to copy: read tcp ... connection timed out`\n\nHere is what you can do next depending on your testing goals:\n\n---\n\n### Option 1: Test with the Active Cloud LLM (No downloads needed)\nSince your containers (`db`, `gateway`, `mcp_server`, and `frontend`) are already running and configured to use **FPT AI (cloud)** by default:\n1. Open [http://localhost:8081](http://localhost:8081) in your browser.\n2. Log in as a teacher (`teacher1@vnexus.vn` / `123456`) or student (`hs01@vnexus.vn` / `123456`).\n3. Create study plans or interact with the tutor. The system is fully operational and queries the FPT Cloud API.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Test Offline Mode Instantly (No Ollama needed)\nIf you want to verify that the app handles offline situations gracefully without waiting for a 3.27 GB image download, you can use the built-in static fallback templates:\n1. Open your [.env](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/.env) file.\n2. Change the mode to:\n   ```env\n   LLM_MODE=offline\n   ```\n3. Apply the changes by restarting the gateway:\n   ```bash\n   docker compose up -d --force-recreate gateway\n   ```\n4. Ask the dashboard to generate a study plan. It will bypass all LLM API calls and instantly return the pre-configured local fallback templates.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Retry pulling local Ollama (Lite CPU version)\nIf you still want to run the local Ollama LLM on your CPU, try pulling it again using the Lite configuration:\n```bash\ndocker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml pull ollama\n```\nOnce the download succeeds, run:\n```bash\ndocker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml up -d\ndocker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml exec ollama ollama pull qwen3:1.7b\n```\nThen update your [.env](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/.env) to `LLM_MODE=ollama` and run:\n```bash\ndocker compose -f docker-compose.lite.yml up -d --force-recreate gateway\n```\n\n***\n\n**Summary of work completed:**\n- Analyzed the docker log indicating a connection timeout during the image pull.\n- Provided concrete next steps to use the running cloud mode, trigger static offline fallback mode (without any large image downloads), or retry the Lite CPU configuration.","thinking":"**Analyzing Network Failure**\n\nI've hit a snag. Task `71e25571-7166-4225-8338-32b4e3317b15/task-60`, attempting to run `docker compose up -d ollama`, timed out during the image pull. The error points to a network connection timeout, specifically a `read tcp` failure on the network. Investigating the Docker network configuration and internet connectivity is the next step to resolve this.\n\n\n**Investigating Offline Mode**\n\nI'm now focusing on a crucial alternative due to the network timeout during the Ollama image pull. I've realized the user can instantly test the offline fallback mode by setting `LLM_MODE=offline` in their `.env` file. This bypasses the need for the large `ollama` download entirely, and lets the user test the whole application instantly. I'll provide clear instructions to edit the `.env` file, offering to assist if needed.\n\n\n"}
