{"step_index":101,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-07-18T07:34:28Z","content":"The test run against the FPT AI Cloud LLM completed. \n\nThe test **actually succeeded in calling the LLM** and got a valid response, but failed only due to a fragile assertion in the test code:\n\n### The Failure Analysis\nIn [tests/test_plan_tool.py](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/tests/test_plan_tool.py) (line 15), the test asserts:\n```python\nassert \"Học sinh\" in plan or \"hệ thống\" in plan or \"lỗ hổng\" in plan or \"ôn\" in plan\n```\n\nHowever, the FPT Cloud LLM returned a friendly, well-formatted response using different words:\n```json\n{\n  \"summary\": \"Em đã nắm khá chắc kỹ năng Present Simple vs Present Continuous với 80% mastery ở trình độ...\",\n  \"closing\": \"Em chỉ còn một bước nhỏ nữa thôi — kiên trì luyện tập 20 phút mỗi ngày là em sẽ đạt mastery 100% ngay!\"\n}\n```\n\nSince the model used **\"Em\"** instead of **\"Học sinh\"** and **\"luyện tập\"** instead of **\"ôn\"**, the test failed the assertion even though the output is correct.\n\n---\n\n### What to do next to optimize and align the tests:\n\nIf you want to optimize your prompts and make the test suite more robust:\n\n1. **Fix the Assertion in Test File**:\n   Open [tests/test_plan_tool.py](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/tests/test_plan_tool.py) and change line 15 to include the actual words used in the friendly prompt, or assert that the returned string is valid JSON:\n   ```python\n   # Example: check for keywords actually generated by the optimized prompt\n   assert any(keyword in plan for keyword in [\"Em\", \"hệ thống\", \"lộ trình\", \"luyện tập\", \"ôn\"])\n   ```\n\n2. **Re-run the tests**:\n   Verify everything passes:\n   ```bash\n   PYTHONPATH=.:gateway pytest\n   ```\n\n***\n\n**Summary of work completed:**\n- Inspected the pytest run logs showing the successful execution of FPT AI completions.\n- Discovered that the failure in `test_generate_training_plan` was only due to a rigid substring check in the test assertion.\n- Provided the exact assertion fix to align the test suite with the optimized prompts.","thinking":"**Analyzing the Failure**\n\nI've just pinpointed a failure in `tests/test_plan_tool.py`, specifically `test_generate_training_plan`. The relevant output is a JSON structure. I need to understand its contents to diagnose the root cause of this pytest failure. I'm focusing on the JSON structure to get the details of the failure.\n\n\n"}
