{"step_index":48,"source":"MODEL","type":"GREP_SEARCH","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-07-18T09:27:41Z","content":"Created At: 2026-07-18T16:27:41+07:00\nCompleted At: 2026-07-18T16:27:41+07:00\n{\"File\":\"/home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC 2026/v-nexus/logs/claude-session/vinc-claude-2026-07-17.log\",\"LineNumber\":953,\"LineContent\":\"{\\\"parentUuid\\\":\\\"69ab4692-9941-4f3e-a485-78b34652aefb\\\",\\\"isSidechain\\\":false,\\\"attachment\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"skill_listing\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"- deep-research: Deep research harness — fan-out web searches, fetch sources, adversarially verify claims, synthesize a cited report. - When the user wants a deep, multi-source, fact-checked research report on any topic. BEFORE invoking, check if the question is specific enough to research directly — if underspecified (e.g., \\\\\\\"what car to buy\\\\\\\" without budget/use-case/region), ask 2-3 clarifying questions to narrow scope. Then pass the refined question as args, weaving the answers in.\\\\n- dataviz: Use this skill whenever you are about to create ANY chart, graph, plot, dashboard, or data visualization, in ANY output medium — an HTML or React artifact, inline SVG, plotting code in any library (matplotlib, plotly, d3, Recharts, …), an image/PNG you will render and upload, or a chart shared into Slack. Read it BEFORE writing the first line of chart code, choosing chart colors, building a stat tile / meter / KPI row, or laying out a dashboard. Produces visualizations that read as one system — elegant, accessible, consistent in light and dark — using a brand-neutral placeholder palette you swap for your own. Teaches a design-system-agnostic method: a form heuristic, a color formula with a runnable validator, mark specs, and interaction rules. A validated default palette is documented in `references/palette.md` — swap that file's values for your brand's. Triggers on: \\\\\\\"chart\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"graph\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"plot\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"data viz\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"visualization\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"dashboard\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"analytics\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"visualize data\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"categorical colors\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"sequential / diverging palette\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"stat tile\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"sparkline\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"heatmap\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"legend\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"axis\\\\\\\", \n<truncated 24901 bytes>\nble, Opus, Sonnet, Haiku, `anthropic`, `@anthropic-ai`, `claude-*`, `us.anthropic.*`, `[1m]`); the user asks about an LLM (pricing/model choice/limits/caching) — never answer from memory; OR the task is LLM-shaped with provider unstated (agent/MCP/tool-definition/multi-agent/RAG/LLM-judge/computer-use; generate/summarize/extract/classify/rewrite/converse over NL; debugging refusals/cutoffs/streaming/tool-calls/tokens).\\\\nSKIP only when another provider is being worked on (overrides all triggers): OpenAI/GPT/Gemini/Llama/Mistral/Cohere/Ollama named in the query; OR `grep -rE 'openai|langchain_openai|google.generativeai|genai|mistralai|cohere|ollama'` over the project hits (run this grep FIRST if no provider named — don't Read the file).\\\\n- run: Launch and drive this project's app to see a change working. Use when asked to run, start, or screenshot the app, or to confirm a change works in the real app (not just tests). First looks for a project skill that already covers launching the app; otherwise falls back to built-in patterns per project type (CLI, server, TUI, Electron, browser-driven, library).\\\\n- init: Initialize a new CLAUDE.md file with codebase documentation\\\\n- review: Review a GitHub pull request; for your working diff use /code-review\\\\n- security-review: Complete a security review of the pending changes on the current branch\\\",\\\"skillCount\\\":17,\\\"isInitial\\\":true,\\\"names\\\":[\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"dataviz\\\",\\\"artifact-design\\\",\\\"artifact-capabilities\\\",\\\"update-config\\\",\\\"keybindings-help\\\",\\\"verify\\\",\\\"code-review\\\",\\\"simplify\\\",\\\"fewer-permission-prompts\\\",\\\"loop\\\",\\\"schedule\\\",\\\"claude-api\\\",\\\"run\\\",\\\"init\\\",\\\"review\\\",\\\"security-review\\\"]},\\\"type\\\":\\\"attachment\\\",\\\"uuid\\\":\\\"03ef57cd-aabc-4bd8-8f4e-956550d8ddea\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-07-17T11:52:28.746Z\\\",\\\"userType\\\":\\\"external\\\",\\\"entrypoint\\\":\\\"claude-vscode\\\",\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/home/hiendc/Documents/VAIC-2026\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"227d4c5c-c4a2-40e5-ae12-dadb723e315c\\\",\\\"version\\\":\\\"2.1.212\\\",\\\"gitBranch\\\":\\\"HEAD\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"dazzling-tickling-goose\\\"}\"}","truncated_fields":["content"]}
{"step_index":49,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-07-18T09:27:41Z","content":"I will edit [gateway/app/config.py](file:///home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC%202026/v-nexus/gateway/app/config.py) to read the new environment variables.","thinking":"**Analyzing Ollama Integration**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on integrating Ollama. My focus has shifted to the `agent/llm_client.py` file. The goal here is to implement a `call_llm()` dispatcher and a `create_message_ollama()` function, and I'm mapping out the implications for the overall architecture.\n\n\n**Refining Tool Integration**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on integrating Ollama. My focus has shifted to the `agent/llm_client.py` file. The goal here is to implement a `call_llm()` dispatcher and a `create_message_ollama()` function, and I'm mapping out the implications for the overall architecture.\n\nUpdating the tools, I'm replacing `create_message_fpt` with `call_llm` in `plan_tool.py`, `teacher_summary_tool.py`, and `parent_summary_tool.py`. I'm going to retain `create_message` for backward compatibility, and I'm going to retain `create_message_fpt` for the time being, to use with `call_llm` in \"fpt\" mode, ensuring it uses the correct config attributes now.\n\n\n**Confirming Ollama Compatibility**\n\nI've confirmed Ollama's OpenAI compatibility, specifically at `/v1`. The `.env` also confirms `OLLAMA_BASE_URL`. I'm going to leverage this to create a clean `create_message_ollama` function, which calls the OpenAI client. I've drafted a dispatcher `call_llm` to route requests based on settings. I need to think about how to check that the service is configured and reachable, as well.\n\n\n**Verifying LLM Availability**\n\nI'm now focusing on a robust `is_llm_available()` function. My current plan involves checking the `llm_mode` setting and API key. I'll include a quick HTTP GET request with a short timeout to the base URL, inside a try-except block, to verify the endpoint's responsiveness. The goal is a fast and reliable check for service availability.\n\n\n**Validating Connectivity Status**\n\nMy current focus is on refining the `is_llm_available()` function for improved reliability. I'm exploring the best way to verify LLM service availability, including a `requests.get` check. My thinking is to target either the base URL or the `/models` endpoint with a short timeout and proper authorization, if needed. I'm carefully considering how to handle various scenarios, especially for the \"fpt\" mode with its specific base URL and API key requirements. I'm making it robust, based on the implementation described.\n\n\n**Improving Availability Checks**\n\nI'm now refining the availability check logic further. Considering scenarios with no internet or local-only CI, I'm integrating a fallback mechanism. If the initial endpoint check fails, I'll fall back to verifying the environment variables are set. I need to be sure that the code is robust enough to handle the potential failure of the network call and ensure a graceful fallback to a basic check of settings, or use the try-except logic in the tool code to determine if the endpoint is truly available.\n\n\n","tool_calls":[{"name":"replace_file_content","args":{"AllowMultiple":"false","Description":"\"Update Settings class to read the new env vars LLM_MODE, API_KEY, LLM_BASE_URL, LLM_MODEL, OLLAMA_BASE_URL, OLLAMA_MODEL\"","EndLine":"20","Instruction":"\"Replace configuration properties with the specified environment variables.\"","ReplacementContent":"\"    llm_mode: str = os.environ.get(\\\"LLM_MODE\\\", \\\"offline\\\")\\n    api_key: str = os.environ.get(\\\"API_KEY\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n    llm_base_url: str = os.environ.get(\\\"LLM_BASE_URL\\\", \\\"https://mkp-api.fptcloud.com/v1\\\")\\n    llm_model: str = os.environ.get(\\\"LLM_MODEL\\\", \\\"GLM-5.2\\\")\\n    ollama_base_url: str = os.environ.get(\\\"OLLAMA_BASE_URL\\\", \\\"http://ollama:11434/v1\\\")\\n    ollama_model: str = os.environ.get(\\\"OLLAMA_MODEL\\\", \\\"qwen3:0.6b\\\")\\n    database_url: str = os.environ.get(\\n        \\\"DATABASE_URL\\\", \\\"postgresql+asyncpg://vnexus:vnexus@localhost:5432/vnexus\\\"\\n    )\\n    mcp_server_url: str = os.environ.get(\\\"MCP_SERVER_URL\\\", \\\"http://mcp_server:8100/mcp\\\")\\n    auth_secret: str = os.environ.get(\\\"AUTH_SECRET\\\", \\\"change-me-dev-only-secret\\\")\"","StartLine":"10","TargetContent":"\"    anthropic_api_key: str = os.environ.get(\\\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n    llm_model: str = os.environ.get(\\\"LLM_MODEL\\\", \\\"claude-sonnet-5\\\")\\n    fpt_api_key: str = os.environ.get(\\\"FPT_API_KEY\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n    fpt_api_base: str = os.environ.get(\\\"FPT_API_BASE\\\", \\\"https://mkp-api.fptcloud.com/v1\\\")\\n    fpt_model: str = os.environ.get(\\\"FPT_MODEL\\\", \\\"DeepSeek-V4-Flash\\\")\\n    database_url: str = os.environ.get(\\n        \\\"DATABASE_URL\\\", \\\"postgresql+asyncpg://vnexus:vnexus@localhost:5432/vnexus\\\"\\n    )\\n    mcp_server_url: str = os.environ.get(\\\"MCP_SERVER_URL\\\", \\\"http://mcp_server:8100/mcp\\\")\\n    auth_secret: str = os.environ.get(\\\"AUTH_SECRET\\\", \\\"change-me-dev-only-secret\\\")\"","TargetFile":"\"/home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC 2026/v-nexus/gateway/app/config.py\"","toolAction":"\"Editing config.py\"","toolSummary":"\"Editing config.py\""}}]}
