{"step_index":91,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-07-18T14:58:23Z","thinking":"**Confirming Setup Success**\n\nI've just confirmed the Python environment setup is perfect! Running the tests with `PYTHONPATH=gateway` executes without a hitch. This confirms the infrastructure is in place, and I can start delving into the user's specific prompt optimization request, namely, \"Bạn hãy code chi tiết phần Tối ưu prompt mà cùng 1 đề khảo sát làm hơn 2 lần mà chưa đạt kết quả.\"\n\n\n**Analyzing Learning Pathways**\n\nI'm now diving into how to structure the alternative learning pathways. I've defined the trigger conditions, specifically looking at student test history to identify repeated attempts with limited improvement. Now, I will implement a python function `generate_alternative_plans`. I have already analyzed and defined parameters like number of attempts, mastery differences, time between submissions and completion rates in the `StudentTestResult` records. I'm focusing on crafting a prompt and JSON schema to elicit three tailored learning paths from the LLM, incorporating the challenges of optimizing these responses.\n\n\n","tool_calls":[{"name":"view_file","args":{"AbsolutePath":"\"/home/hieu/Downloads/Code/VAIC 2026/v-nexus/tests/test_plan_tool.py\"","toolAction":"\"Viewing tests/test_plan_tool.py\"","toolSummary":"\"View tests/test_plan_tool.py\""}}]}
