{"step_index":95,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-07-18T14:58:29Z","thinking":"**Analyzing Database Connection**\n\nI've been examining the connection established by `TestClient(app)` within `test_gateway_health.py`. It appears `init_db()` is called under lifespan, which means the test client is connecting to PostgreSQL when it runs. This is critical for understanding the health check's interaction with the database.\n\n\n**Investigating Database Interactions**\n\nI'm now digging into how the test environment sets up database connections. I believe it's either using Docker containers or a local Postgres instance, confirmed by the passing test. Moving forward, I am planning to modify the code. I will add `alternative_plans` to `StudentTestResult` and update the database schema using `ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS alternative_plans JSON;`. I'll also add `alternative_plans` to `TestResultResponse` and update `submit_placement_test` to consider prior attempts. I will do this by querying existing test results and implementing specific trigger conditions based on attempt number and timestamps.\n\n\n**Examining Attempt Logic**\n\nI'm now focusing on implementing the logic for handling previous test attempts. I'm calculating the time gap between attempts and setting a configurable threshold (currently 10 minutes). I'm also calculating the completion rate using the number of answers provided versus the total questions in the test (using `test.question_links` to get the count). My next step is to determine if mastery has significantly improved between attempts by comparing percentage scores.\n\n\n","tool_calls":[{"name":"replace_file_content","args":{"AllowMultiple":"false","Description":"\"Add alternative_plans column to StudentTestResult model\"","EndLine":"165","Instruction":"\"Add alternative_plans column to StudentTestResult model in db/models.py\"","ReplacementContent":"\"    training_plan: Mapped[Optional[str]] = mapped_column(Te